[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6505,
        "end_time": 8807,
        "text": "Water is virtually everywhere,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8807,
        "end_time": 11259,
        "text": "from soil moisture and ice caps,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11259,
        "end_time": 14086,
        "text": "to the cells inside our own bodies."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14086,
        "end_time": 16181,
        "text": "Depending on factors like location,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 16181,
        "end_time": 17399,
        "text": "fat index,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 17399,
        "end_time": 18114,
        "text": "age,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 18114,
        "end_time": 19202,
        "text": "and sex,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 19202,
        "end_time": 23808,
        "text": "the average human is between 55-60% water."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 23808,
        "end_time": 27024,
        "text": "At birth, human babies are even wetter."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 27024,
        "end_time": 32307,
        "text": "Being 75% water, \nthey are swimmingly similar to fish."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 32307,
        "end_time": 37331,
        "text": "But their water composition drops to 65%\nby their first birthday."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 37331,
        "end_time": 40196,
        "text": "So what role does water \nplay in our bodies,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 40196,
        "end_time": 44288,
        "text": "and how much do we actually need to drink\nto stay healthy?"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 44288,
        "end_time": 48529,
        "text": "The H20 in our bodies works to cushion\nand lubricate joints,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 48529,
        "end_time": 49948,
        "text": "regulate temperature,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 49948,
        "end_time": 53932,
        "text": "and to nourish the brain and spinal cord."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 53932,
        "end_time": 56062,
        "text": "Water isn&#39;t only in our blood."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 56062,
        "end_time": 60510,
        "text": "An adult&#39;s brain and heart are almost\nthree quarters water."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 60510,
        "end_time": 64367,
        "text": "That&#39;s roughly equivalent to the amount\nof moisture in a banana."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 64367,
        "end_time": 68487,
        "text": "Lungs are more similar to an apple at 83%."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 68487,
        "end_time": 74310,
        "text": "And even seemingly dry human bones\nare 31% water."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 74310,
        "end_time": 76051,
        "text": "If we are essentially made of water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 76051,
        "end_time": 77634,
        "text": "and surrounded by water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 77634,
        "end_time": 80492,
        "text": "why do we still need to drink so much?"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 80492,
        "end_time": 84293,
        "text": "Well, each day we lose two to three liters\nthrough our sweat,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 84293,
        "end_time": 85227,
        "text": "urine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 85227,
        "end_time": 86707,
        "text": "and bowel movements,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 86707,
        "end_time": 88371,
        "text": "and even just from breathing."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 88371,
        "end_time": 90859,
        "text": "While these functions \nare essential to our survival,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 90859,
        "end_time": 93306,
        "text": "we need to compensate for the fluid loss."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 93306,
        "end_time": 97848,
        "text": "Maintaining a balanced water level\nis essential to avoid dehydration"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 97848,
        "end_time": 99710,
        "text": "or over-hydration,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 99710,
        "end_time": 103279,
        "text": "both of which can have devastating\neffects on overall health."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 103279,
        "end_time": 105404,
        "text": "At first detection of low water levels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 105404,
        "end_time": 108367,
        "text": "sensory receptors \nin the brain&#39;s hypothalamus"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 108367,
        "end_time": 111399,
        "text": "signal the release \nof antidiuretic hormone."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 111399,
        "end_time": 114489,
        "text": "When it reached the kidneys, \nit creates aquaporins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 114489,
        "end_time": 120445,
        "text": "special channels that enable blood\nto absorb and retain more water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 120445,
        "end_time": 123050,
        "text": "leading to concentrated, dark urine."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 123050,
        "end_time": 126555,
        "text": "Increased dehydration can cause\nnotable drops in energy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 126555,
        "end_time": 127586,
        "text": "mood,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 127586,
        "end_time": 128774,
        "text": "skin moisture,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 128774,
        "end_time": 130198,
        "text": "and blood pressure,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 130198,
        "end_time": 133252,
        "text": "as well as signs of cognitive impairment."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 133252,
        "end_time": 137210,
        "text": "A dehydrated brain works harder \nto accomplish the same amount"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 137210,
        "end_time": 138696,
        "text": "as a normal brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 138696,
        "end_time": 142618,
        "text": "and it even temporarily shrinks\nbecause of its lack of water."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 142618,
        "end_time": 145614,
        "text": "Over-hydration, or hyponatremia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 145614,
        "end_time": 150669,
        "text": "is usually caused by overconsumption\nof water in a short amount of time."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 150669,
        "end_time": 153242,
        "text": "Athletes are often the victims \nof over-hydration"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 153242,
        "end_time": 156585,
        "text": "because of complications \nin regulating water levels"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 156585,
        "end_time": 159263,
        "text": "in extreme physical conditions."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 159263,
        "end_time": 163769,
        "text": "Whereas the dehydrated brain amps\nup the production of antidiuretic hormone,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 163769,
        "end_time": 169174,
        "text": "the over-hydrated brain slows,\nor even stops, releasing it into the blood."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 169174,
        "end_time": 171980,
        "text": "Sodium electrolytes in the body\nbecome diluted,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 171980,
        "end_time": 174133,
        "text": "causing cells to swell."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 174133,
        "end_time": 175584,
        "text": "In severe cases,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 175584,
        "end_time": 179768,
        "text": "the kidneys can&#39;t keep up with \nthe resulting volumes of dilute urine."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 179768,
        "end_time": 181923,
        "text": "Water intoxication then occurs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 181923,
        "end_time": 183559,
        "text": "possibly causing headache,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 183559,
        "end_time": 184688,
        "text": "vomiting,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 184688,
        "end_time": 188162,
        "text": "and, in rare instances, seizures\nor death."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 188162,
        "end_time": 190295,
        "text": "But that&#39;s a pretty extreme situation."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 190295,
        "end_time": 192062,
        "text": "On a normal, day-to-day basis,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 192062,
        "end_time": 195632,
        "text": "maintaining a well-hydrated system\nis easy to manage"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 195632,
        "end_time": 199528,
        "text": "for those of us fortunate enough \nto have access to clean drinking water."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 199528,
        "end_time": 203808,
        "text": "For a long time, conventional wisdom said\nthat we should drink eight glasses a day."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 203808,
        "end_time": 206453,
        "text": "That estimate has since been fine-tuned."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 206453,
        "end_time": 210245,
        "text": "Now, the consensus is that the amount\nof water we need to imbibe"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 210245,
        "end_time": 213116,
        "text": "depends largely on our weight\nand environment."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 213116,
        "end_time": 219616,
        "text": "The recommended daily intake varies from\nbetween 2.5-3.7 liters of water for men,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 219616,
        "end_time": 222802,
        "text": "and about 2-2.7 liters for women,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 222802,
        "end_time": 226148,
        "text": "a range that is pushed up \nor down if we are healthy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 226148,
        "end_time": 226987,
        "text": "active,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 226987,
        "end_time": 227950,
        "text": "old,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 227950,
        "end_time": 229663,
        "text": "or overheating."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 229663,
        "end_time": 231522,
        "text": "While water is the healthiest hydrator,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 231522,
        "end_time": 232617,
        "text": "other beverages,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 232617,
        "end_time": 235230,
        "text": "even those with caffeine \nlike coffee or tea,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 235230,
        "end_time": 237323,
        "text": "replenish fluids as well."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 237323,
        "end_time": 242306,
        "text": "And water within food makes up \nabout a fifth of our daily H20 intake."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 242306,
        "end_time": 244333,
        "text": "Fruits and vegetables like strawberries,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 244333,
        "end_time": 245302,
        "text": "cucumbers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 245302,
        "end_time": 248874,
        "text": "and even broccoli are over 90% water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 248874,
        "end_time": 254119,
        "text": "and can supplement liquid intake while\nproviding valuable nutrients and fiber."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 254119,
        "end_time": 257276,
        "text": "Drinking well might also have various\nlong-term benefits."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 257276,
        "end_time": 261618,
        "text": "Studies have shown that optimal hydration\ncan lower the chance of stroke,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 261618,
        "end_time": 263107,
        "text": "help manage diabetes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 263107,
        "end_time": 267871,
        "text": "and potentially reduce the risk\nof certain types of cancer."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 267871,
        "end_time": 272051,
        "text": "No matter what, getting the right amount\nof liquid makes a world of difference"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 272051,
        "end_time": 273338,
        "text": "in how you&#39;ll feel,"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 273338,
        "end_time": 274205,
        "text": "think,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 274205,
        "end_time": 276073,
        "text": "and function day to day."
    }
]